nel panel-full-width-1 full-page-width"> <div class="inner"> <div class="panel-pane pane-aclu-components-share-icons share-icons" > <ul><li class="facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/v3.1/dialog/feed?app_id=782898798486624&amp;link=https%3A//www.aclu.org/news/nsa-collating-data-americans-facebook-gps-tax-other-records&amp;name=NSA%20Collating%20Data%20on%20Americans%20From%20Facebook%2C%20GPS%2C%20Tax%2C%20Other%20Records&amp;redirect_uri=https%3A//www.aclu.org/news/nsa-collating-data-americans-facebook-gps-tax-other-records" target="_blank" title="Submit this to Facebook">Facebook</a></li><li class="twitter"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=American%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union&amp;via=aclu&amp;title=NSA%20Collating%20Data%20on%20Americans%20From%20Facebook%2C%20GPS%2C%20Tax%2C%20Other%20Records&amp;url=https%3A//www.aclu.org/news/nsa-collating-data-americans-facebook-gps-tax-other-records" target="_blank" title="Submit this to Twitter">Twitter</a></li><li class="reddit"><a href="http://reddit.com/submit?title=NSA%20Collating%20Data%20on%20Americans%20From%20Facebook%2C%20GPS%2C%20Tax%2C%20Other%20Records%20%7C%20American%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union&amp;url=https%3A//www.aclu.org/news/nsa-collating-data-americans-facebook-gps-tax-other-records" target="_blank" title="Submit this to Reddit">Reddit</a></li><li class="email"><a href="mailto:?body=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aclu.org%2Fnews%2Fnsa-collating-data-americans-facebook-gps-tax-other-records%0D%0A%0D%0AFOR IMMEDIATE RELEASECONTACT:Â media@aclu.orgNEW YORK â With the goal of mapping peopleâs social relationships, the National Security Agency is secretly collecting information on Americans from a previously unknown array of public and commercial sources, according to a report today from The New York Times. The data sources include âbank codes, insurance information, Facebook profiles, passenger manifests, voter registration rolls and GPS location information, as well as property records and unspecified tax data,â the article said.&amp;subject=NSA%20Collating%20Data%20on%20Americans%20From%20Facebook%2C%20GPS%2C%20Tax%2C%20Other%20Records%20%7C%20American%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union" target="_blank" title="Submit this to Email">Email</a></li><li class="print"><a href="/print/node/18608" target="_blank" title="Submit this to Print">Print</a></li></ul> </div> </div> </div> <div class="center-wrapper clearfix full-page-width"> <div class="inner"> <div class="panel-panel panel-main-1 content-column"> <div class="panel-pane pane-entity-field pane-node-field-date date" > <div class="field-date"> <span class="date-display-single">September 28, 2013</span> </div> </div> <div class="panel-pane pane-entity-field pane-node-body" > <div class="field-body text-area"> <p>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</p> <p>CONTACT:Â <a href="mailto:media@aclu.org">media@aclu.org</a></p> <p>NEW YORK â With the goal of mapping peopleâs social relationships, the National Security Agency is secretly collecting information on Americans from a previously unknown array of public and commercial sources, according to a report today from The New York Times. The data sources include âbank codes, insurance information, Facebook profiles, passenger manifests, voter registration rolls and GPS location information, as well as property records and unspecified tax data,â the article said.</p> <p>American Civil Liberties Union Deputy Legal Director Jameel Jaffer had this reaction:</p> <blockquote> <p>This report confirms what whistleblowers have been saying for years: the NSA has been monitoring virtually every aspect of Americans' lives â their communications, their associations, even their locations.Â Â The NSA apparently believes it can conduct this surveillance because 30 years ago the Supreme Court upheld the governmentâs warrantless collection of basic information about a criminal suspect's telephone calls over the course of a single day. But the claim that this narrow case from the analog era authorizes the mass surveillance of hundreds of millions of Americans is outlandish. That the NSAâs surveillance activities rest on so flimsy a foundation is further evidence that our intelligence-oversight system is utterly broken.</p> </blockquote> <p>More information on NSA spying is at:</p> <p><a href="https://owa.aclu.org/exchweb/bin/redir.asp?URL=http://www.aclu.org/time-rein-surveillance-state-0" target="_blank">aclu.org/nsa-surveillance</a></p> </div> </div> </div> <div class="panel-panel panel-right-1 sidebar-right"> <div class="panel-pane pane-aclu-components-issue-area related-issues" > <div class=issues-vertical><h2>Related Issues</h2><div class="item-list"><ul><li class="first"><a href="/search/%20?f%5B0%5D=field_issues%3A142&amp;f%5B1%5D=type%3Apress_release">Privacy and Surveillance</a></li> <li class="last"><a href="/search/%20?f%5B0%5D=field_issues%3A132&amp;f%5B1%5D=type%3Apress_release">National Security</a></li> </ul></div></div> </div> <div class="panel-pane pane-featured-action" > <article class="node-69924 node node-action view-mode-featured_action action-background-style-featured_image clearfix component action featured-action"> <div class="inner"> <header> <h2 class="node__title node-title"><a href="https://action.aclu.org/petition/stop-harassing-travelers?ms_aff=NAT&initms_aff=NAT&ms=180822_nationalsecurity_religiousliberty_zainab&initms=180822_nationalsecurity_religiousliberty_zainab&ms_chan=web&initms_chan=web"><span>DHS: Stop Harassing Airport Travelers Like Zainab</span></a></h2> </header> <div class="field-image"> <a href="https://action.aclu.org/petition/stop-harassing-travelers?ms_aff=NAT&amp;amp%3Binitms_aff=NAT&amp;amp%3Bms=180822_nationalsecurity_religiousliberty_zainab&amp;amp%3Binitms=180822_nationalsecurity_religiousliberty_zainab&amp;amp%3Bms_chan=web&amp;amp%3Binitms_chan=web"><img data-src="https://www.aclu.org/sites/default/files/styles/action_sidebar_wide_280x240/public/field_image/action2400x960_copy_copy.jpg?itok=DGTkETHW" class="lazyload" width="280" height="240" alt="" /></a> </div> <div class="field-action-link"> <div class="field-items"> <div class="field-item even"> <!-- Adding an arrow span next to link --> <a href="https://action.aclu.org/petition/stop-harassing-travelers?ms_aff=NAT&amp;initms_aff=NAT&amp;ms=180822_nationalsecurity_religiousliberty_zainab&amp;initms=180822_nationalsecurity_religiousliberty_zainab&amp;ms_chan=web&amp;initms_chan=web">Add your name<span class="arrow"></span></a> </div> </div> </div> </div> </article> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div><div id="block-aclu-social-stay-informed" class="block block-aclu-social last even"> <div class="inner"> <div class="inner-inner"> <h2 class="block__title block-title">Stay Informed</h2> <form action="/news/nsa-collating-data-americans-facebook-gps-tax-other-records?redirect=national-security/nsa-collating-data-americans-facebook-gps-tax-other-records" method="post" id="aclu-social-signup-form--2" accept-charset="UTF-8"><div><div class="form-item form-type-textfield form-item-signup-email"> <label class="element-invisible" for="edit-signup-email--2">Email Address <span class="form-required" title="This field is required.">*</span></label> <input placeholder="Your email address" type="text" id="edit-signup-email--2" name="signup_email" value="" size="60" maxlength="128" class="form-text required" /> </div> <div class="form-item form-type-textfield form-item-signup-zip"> <label class="element-invisible" for="edit-signup-zip--2">ZIP Code <span class="form-required" title="This field is required.">*</span></label> <input placeholder="ZIP code" type="text" id="edit-signup-zip--2" name="signup_zip" value="" size="60" maxlength="128" class="form-text required" /> </div> <input type="hidden" name="location" value="footer" /> <input type="submit" id="edit-submit--2" name="op" value="Join our newsletter" class="form-submit" /><input type="hidden" name="form_build_id" value="form-ycrK_SPHjoyU-7loJoUkRLcOV51RTiTvaUXRT2qjB